1
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:53,349
INSIDE
PARIS

2
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:07,638
No mistake.
This is an apostrophe.

3
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:13,155
I'm speaking to you, dear viewer.

4
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,192
But, like you, I...

5
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:21,716
I'm aware of
the intolerably embarrassing odour

6
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:26,430
of someone who dares
speak directly to the audience.

7
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:31,396
But I'll do it to begin this story
with an introduction.

8
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:37,432
What I have in mind
isn't just verbose and pedantic

9
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,954
beyond my wildest dreams...

10
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:45,630
Without spoiling anything,
it's also horribly personal.

11
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,918
Back to the introduction...

12
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:56,233
Despite the evidence, I'm not this story's hero.

13
00:03:58,120 --> 00:04:01,510
So I'll give myself the right to be the narrator.

14
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:03,915
Besides,

15
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:10,434
that suits well my characteristic omniscience.

16
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:13,318
Despite the doubts confessed to you

17
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:15,916
by some of the young girls I know,

18
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:20,308
those little lovelies have no idea.

19
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:24,395
But I can be everywhere at once.

20
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:28,758
<i>Like here, in the middle of France.</i>

21
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,637
<i>A potato-shaped region.</i>

22
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:33,550
<i>A year ago, my brother Paul...</i>

23
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:37,629
<i>You saw him earlier in my bed...</i>
<i>He left the city</i>

24
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,153
<i>to move there.</i>

25
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:42,391
<i>He didn't go alone,</i>
<i>but with Anna and Loup.</i>

26
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,913
<i>He's Anna's son.</i>

27
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:47,478
<i>To justify leaving, he lamely assured me</i>

28
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:51,155
<i>that life would be easier</i>
<i>in the countryside than Paris.</i>

29
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,998
<i>Without a smile,</i>

30
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:58,117
<i>he argued he needed distance</i>
<i>between him and us.</i>

31
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:02,475
<i>I never mentioned his confession.</i>

32
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:04,675
<i>I should have.</i>

33
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:07,077
<i>I should have stopped him.</i>

34
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:11,276
I never should have let Paul go
without begging him to stay.

35
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:17,311
If I had stopped him,
the rest wouldn't have happened.

36
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:20,158
I'll shut up now.

37
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:22,549
This is an intro, not a guided tour.

38
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:27,836
I'll turn back into a character
who doesn't know you nor the plot.

39
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:30,309
That small privilege is my right.

40
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:33,151
Just one last question...

41
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,676
Maybe your viewing experience
outdoes what I've already lived.

42
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:41,673
Is it really possible

43
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:45,273
for a love story to make us jump off a bridge?

44
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,634
Wow!

45
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,676
Looks like a serious event.

46
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:37,715
Not really.

47
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,198
White shirt!

48
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:43,829
What's with your new craze?

49
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,797
Showering immediately after?

50
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:48,314
Anna, I don't have time to fight.

51
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,438
Sorry. Did I hurt you?

52
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:57,318
Leave me alone, asshole. Get dressed.

53
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,112
I'll tell you why you shower.

54
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,074
Three reasons.

55
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:12,668
First, so I see it tires you out.

56
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:15,915
You only fuck me for nostalgia's sake.

57
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:20,036
Your twisted way of being faithful.
To what, I don't know.

58
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:22,953
That's all I am in your eyes, an old memory.

59
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,235
- Second reason.
- Shut up.

60
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,719
Get dressed.

61
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,119
Second reason.

62
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,794
You don't want to offend me, contradict me.

63
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:40,236
Coward! You'd rather fuck me
than admit you don't want me.

64
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,910
Love me too much to hurt me, is that it?

65
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,513
Your love is more about loyalty to the past.

66
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:57,199
The idea of hurting me terrorises you.

67
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,508
Are you listening?

68
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,874
It terrorises you!

69
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,234
Third reason.

70
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:13,595
<i>You shower because you hope I will.</i>

71
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:17,835
<i>You don't dare tell me I stink,</i>
<i>my odours disgust you.</i>

72
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:22,949
<i>You run to the shower, praying I'll follow you,</i>

73
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,352
praying I'll lather up.

74
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:29,158
Seriously, Anna, I have to go.

75
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:33,277
I'm speaking seriously.

76
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:35,078
I've never been more serious.

77
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:37,037
What are you after?

78
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:40,115
I'm after a reason for your inelegance.

79
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:45,113
Despite your nice white shirts
with their impeccably ironed collars,

80
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:48,633
you're about as elegant as a pile of shit,
sweetheart.

81
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,709
It's cruel to act like you made a mistake.

82
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:58,872
Like you can't stay in bed.
Like you must shower.

83
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,472
Like "What have I done?"

84
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:04,111
Like "Sorry I ever fucked you."

85
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,394
What are you saying?

86
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:10,398
You're forcing yourself, Paul.

87
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:13,590
I won't hear this right now.

88
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,958
But you will.

89
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,836
You expect me to speak for you,

90
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,756
to destroy everything, then leave.

91
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,154
Well, fine.

92
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:38,472
I'm ready to destroy everything.

93
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,995
No need to get out.
I'll say goodbye here.

94
00:09:46,680 --> 00:09:48,910
- I'll call you from Paris.
- When are you back?

95
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,673
Three, four days.
By Saturday, for sure.

96
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:54,311
I could drive you and sleep at Dad's.

97
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,960
And Loup? I'd rather you stay with him.

98
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:01,395
Fuck you.

99
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,429
Bye, Loup!

100
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,075
I'll be back.

101
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,312
- Need a light?
- Yes, thanks.

102
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,833
So we're out of love?

103
