518
00:46:41,200 --> 00:46:43,555
- My shitty life.
- Stop pressuring me!

519
00:46:43,640 --> 00:46:47,792
You're not the only shit in my life.
Just a small part.

520
00:46:47,880 --> 00:46:49,916
You're right! Just don't say it!

521
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:51,831
Don't start. I'm not in the mood.

522
00:46:51,920 --> 00:46:52,909
Sorry.

523
00:46:57,560 --> 00:46:58,959
When will I see you again?

524
00:47:00,960 --> 00:47:02,632
Your decision, princess.

525
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:07,750
You want to see me again? Sincerely?

526
00:47:12,320 --> 00:47:15,676
If you assure me it's good for you, OK.

527
00:47:15,760 --> 00:47:16,749
OK.

528
00:47:18,120 --> 00:47:21,829
But here is too complicated.
I don't want my mother to know.

529
00:47:21,920 --> 00:47:23,751
We'll go to my house.

530
00:47:24,920 --> 00:47:26,035
Sure?

531
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:31,713
It's you who won't come
to my neighbourhood!

532
00:47:31,800 --> 00:47:32,869
I'll come.

533
00:47:33,680 --> 00:47:35,955
Alice, it's 4. I have to go.

534
00:47:39,640 --> 00:47:41,870
I'll come, hear me?

535
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:43,678
- What?
- I'll come!

536
00:47:43,760 --> 00:47:46,115
Yes, you'll come.
You'll be most welcome.

537
00:47:58,040 --> 00:48:01,794
I believe you. Do what you want.
No need to explain.

538
00:48:05,560 --> 00:48:08,757
It's 4:40. It took you seven hours
to go to Bon Marché!

539
00:48:08,840 --> 00:48:09,955
That's good!

540
00:48:10,920 --> 00:48:12,558
Very good.

541
00:48:14,640 --> 00:48:16,471
Yeah, if you want.

542
00:48:17,280 --> 00:48:18,838
OK, in 15 minutes.

543
00:48:23,240 --> 00:48:25,470
Your brother missed class today?

544
00:48:26,720 --> 00:48:30,076
That's the last time I pay his tuition.

545
00:48:30,160 --> 00:48:31,832
Next year, he's on his own.

546
00:48:31,920 --> 00:48:33,672
I won't be taken for a fool.

547
00:48:39,240 --> 00:48:40,992
He'll have to ask his mother

548
00:48:42,280 --> 00:48:44,714
to pay for his studies.

549
00:48:51,080 --> 00:48:54,755
Don't stay out in bare feet. You'll catch a chill.

550
00:49:02,640 --> 00:49:07,316
Come in, Paul. We'll decorate the tree.

551
00:49:40,280 --> 00:49:43,909
It's been a long time since we've had a tree.

552
00:49:44,000 --> 00:49:46,150
Not since Claire died.

553
00:49:49,240 --> 00:49:50,639
You're right.

554
00:49:51,800 --> 00:49:52,949
12 years.

555
00:49:55,080 --> 00:49:58,152
I don't keep track of such anniversaries.

556
00:50:01,680 --> 00:50:02,908
Sorry.

557
00:50:03,720 --> 00:50:06,154
It's not forbidden to talk about your sister.

558
00:50:06,240 --> 00:50:08,071
I never forbid anyone.

559
00:50:08,840 --> 00:50:10,239
Don't get mad.

560
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:12,028
I'm not mad.

561
00:50:13,040 --> 00:50:15,349
You're always accusing me of something.

562
00:50:16,600 --> 00:50:18,750
Your brother probably forgot his key.

563
00:50:22,360 --> 00:50:23,509
Oh, it's you.

564
00:50:24,120 --> 00:50:25,075
Is he there?

565
00:50:29,880 --> 00:50:32,348
I knew your father was exaggerating.

566
00:50:32,440 --> 00:50:34,749
You don't look like you're dying.

567
00:50:34,840 --> 00:50:37,149
I'm happy to see you, sweetie.

568
00:50:38,040 --> 00:50:39,519
How handsome you are!

569
00:50:40,400 --> 00:50:41,879
More and more handsome.

570
00:50:48,120 --> 00:50:49,712
You got a tree!

571
00:50:50,400 --> 00:50:52,391
The three of us together for Christmas.

572
00:50:53,520 --> 00:50:55,715
A way of telling me I'm not invited.

573
00:51:04,920 --> 00:51:06,751
Your father's as elegant as ever.

574
00:51:10,920 --> 00:51:15,596
So, tell me. You gave up on the provinces?

575
00:51:15,680 --> 00:51:17,716
I don't know yet. For now, I'm here.

576
00:51:19,720 --> 00:51:21,711
Didn't I warn you it turns you mad?

577
00:51:22,200 --> 00:51:26,352
You wanted to prove God knows what.
But country life isn't for us.

578
00:51:26,440 --> 00:51:28,635
Don't be silly. Want some coffee?

579
00:51:28,720 --> 00:51:30,870
I'm not silly.
Playing farmer like that!

580
00:51:32,160 --> 00:51:34,355
I didn't go to become a farmer.

581
00:51:34,440 --> 00:51:35,668
I know.

582
00:51:37,280 --> 00:51:38,315
So?

583
00:51:39,160 --> 00:51:40,388
Tell me.

584
00:51:42,040 --> 00:51:43,519
You have heartaches?

585
00:51:46,160 --> 00:51:47,593
No.

586
00:51:47,680 --> 00:51:50,319
Your dad told me she left.
Don't lie.

587
00:51:55,480 --> 00:51:57,277
I don't want to talk to you about this.

588
00:51:59,480 --> 00:52:02,153
Nothing to say?
Then I'm here for nothing.

589
00:52:05,440 --> 00:52:06,668
Bravo!

590
00:52:06,760 --> 00:52:07,954
Really!

591
00:52:08,040 --> 00:52:09,598
Perfect!

592
00:52:28,320 --> 00:52:31,118
It's easy not to answer!
I made it, I'm here.

593
00:52:31,960 --> 00:52:34,633
The lights are beautiful!

594
00:52:34,720 --> 00:52:37,553
Come on, I'm waiting for you.
Put on your cap and mittens.

595
00:52:37,640 --> 00:52:39,870
OK, brother? Big kiss.

596
00:52:57,840 --> 00:53:00,070
Oh, it's you. Where are you?

597
00:53:01,200 --> 00:53:02,838
No, I can't pass him to you.

598
00:53:03,440 --> 00:53:04,759
No, Jonathan!

599
00:53:05,680 --> 00:53:06,999
I said no.

600
00:53:24,640 --> 00:53:26,631
We're fine, just fine.

601
00:53:37,960 --> 00:53:38,915
Idiots!

602
00:54:26,640 --> 00:54:29,632
Can I possibly kiss you?
It's a question of life or death.

603
00:54:34,080 --> 00:54:35,229
Go on.

604
00:54:53,400 --> 00:54:54,674
That's nifty.

605
00:54:56,200 --> 00:55:00,432
Nifty? No one says nifty any more.

606
00:55:01,600 --> 00:55:02,749
What should I say?

607
00:55:03,440 --> 00:55:05,192
I don't know.

608
00:55:05,280 --> 00:55:06,474
For nifty?

609
00:55:06,560 --> 00:55:09,518
You could say cool, good,

610
00:55:09,600 --> 00:55:11,909
hot, kick-ass, the bomb.

611
00:55:12,320 --> 00:55:14,470
Or even groovy.

612
00:55:43,280 --> 00:55:45,236
- Did he tell you anything?
- No.

613
00:55:45,320 --> 00:55:47,038
I tried hard, though.

614
00:55:47,120 --> 00:55:50,112
He wouldn't tell me anything either.

615
00:55:51,000 --> 00:55:52,718
He doesn't want to talk to us.

616
00:55:53,440 --> 00:55:54,668
He said that?

617
00:55:56,080 --> 00:55:59,629
He said the only person he wants
to talk to is Claire.

618
00:56:03,880 --> 00:56:05,154
Want to eat?

619
00:56:06,920 --> 00:56:08,239
No, I should go back.

620
00:56:11,560 --> 00:56:13,312
That's a big tree.

621
00:56:16,280 --> 00:56:19,670
Earlier, I thought he would
jump off the balcony.

622
00:56:19,760 --> 00:56:21,318
Don't exaggerate.

623
00:56:21,400 --> 00:56:23,311
I'm not.

624
00:56:24,640 --> 00:56:28,155
Is it normal your son
wants to talk to his dead sister?

625
00:56:30,800 --> 00:56:33,473
He said nothing to Jonathan?

626
00:56:34,840 --> 00:56:37,593
Jonathan should question him first.

627
00:56:37,680 --> 00:56:40,831
He's getting more and more selfish.
That kid's getting worse and worse.

628
00:56:41,560 --> 00:56:43,596
Complain about your son. Go on.

629
00:56:44,520 --> 00:56:46,875
You only see him once a month.
Easy for you!

630
00:56:46,960 --> 00:56:50,270
Must we argue, Mirko?
You really want to fight?

631
00:56:50,360 --> 00:56:52,078
No, I don't!

632
00:56:52,680 --> 00:56:54,875
Here's your coffee, dear.

633
00:56:55,480 --> 00:56:57,436
I think he should see someone.

634
00:56:58,160 --> 00:56:59,832
Maybe start on meds.

635
00:56:59,920 --> 00:57:01,114
You want to drug him.

636
00:57:01,200 --> 00:57:03,191
That's it. Exactly.

637
00:57:03,280 --> 00:57:04,872
I want to drug my son.

638
00:57:05,560 --> 00:57:08,677
There are other ways to get well
besides tranquilizers.

639
00:57:13,920 --> 00:57:18,436
Happiness can be found not only through pills.

640
00:57:20,680 --> 00:57:22,477
I want to call Anna.

641
00:57:22,960 --> 00:57:26,430
That's the last thing you should do.

642
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:29,914
Paul's heart is too fragile.

643
00:57:30,680 --> 00:57:32,318
He's like his father.

644
00:57:32,400 --> 00:57:33,958
Oh Mirko, please!

645
00:57:34,040 --> 00:57:35,792
Think what you want, but it's true.

646
00:57:37,720 --> 00:57:41,030
I think your heart's healthy.

647
00:57:41,760 --> 00:57:43,910
I'm worried about your brain.

648
00:57:44,600 --> 00:57:46,989
Did you see the neurologist again?

649
00:57:48,760 --> 00:57:51,593
I'm sure Anna has the answer.

650
00:57:52,920 --> 00:57:54,717
Maybe something bad happened.

651
00:57:54,800 --> 00:57:58,554
The answer to what?
It's just you're all so closed.

652
00:57:58,640 --> 00:58:00,756
None of you listen to the questions!

653
00:58:01,480 --> 00:58:05,632
Paul acts like his father.
He thinks no one can help.

654
00:58:06,640 --> 00:58:08,073
I don't need a neurologist.

655
00:58:08,160 --> 00:58:10,754
And Paul doesn't need your help to get better!

656
00:58:11,800 --> 00:58:14,234
See how stupid that sounds?

657
00:58:19,440 --> 00:58:20,668
Fine!

658
00:58:21,320 --> 00:58:24,392
Don't make yourself sick.
You're not the worst of fathers.

659
00:58:26,480 --> 00:58:27,959
What's for dinner?

660
00:58:31,080 --> 00:58:32,308
Chicken soup.

661
00:58:32,400 --> 00:58:33,833
How festive!

662
00:58:34,360 --> 00:58:36,430
I'll have some with you.

663
00:58:37,720 --> 00:58:40,359
If your invitation still stands?

664
00:58:55,440 --> 00:58:57,192
Money problems at the moment?

665
00:58:57,280 --> 00:58:58,679
Why do you ask?

666
00:58:58,760 --> 00:59:00,079
I don't know.

667
00:59:00,160 --> 00:59:01,718
Because of the chicken soup.

668
00:59:02,280 --> 00:59:03,474
I'm fine.

669
00:59:04,240 --> 00:59:05,912
We can help, you know.

670
00:59:06,880 --> 00:59:08,871
I'm sure you can't hold out long.

671
00:59:08,960 --> 00:59:11,155
All three of you on your pension.

672
00:59:11,240 --> 00:59:13,879
Your guy already supports you.

673
00:59:13,960 --> 00:59:16,235
Must he pay for your ex-husband, too?

674
00:59:17,640 --> 00:59:19,073
Brilliant!

675
00:59:21,000 --> 00:59:23,719
You brought up money.
You brought it up!

676
00:59:23,800 --> 00:59:27,156
I brought it up because you're in the shithouse.

677
00:59:29,320 --> 00:59:31,515
Don't say shit so much!

678
00:59:32,560 --> 00:59:34,357
That's not very elegant.

679
00:59:36,120 --> 00:59:37,633
You're so stupid!

680
00:59:40,240 --> 00:59:41,593
Really stupid.

681
01:00:02,800 --> 01:00:04,233
Mum!

682
01:00:23,360 --> 01:00:25,351
- Did she leave?
- Yes.

683
01:00:26,480 --> 01:00:27,629
Did you fight?

684
01:00:29,040 --> 01:00:30,234
The usual.

685
01:00:31,560 --> 01:00:33,073
Where's the TV guide?

686
01:00:33,800 --> 01:00:37,429
On the table, or maybe your brother
took it to the toilet.

687
01:00:45,320 --> 01:00:47,151
Forty Gun on cable?

688
01:00:47,240 --> 01:00:49,674
Yeah, sure.

689
01:00:53,280 --> 01:00:57,273
You know, I didn't want to jump
off the balcony earlier.

690
01:00:57,360 --> 01:01:00,033
I saw you thought I wanted to, but I didn't.

691
01:01:00,120 --> 01:01:02,315
I was looking at my phone that fell.

692
01:01:08,560 --> 01:01:11,757
Listen to me and don't interrupt.
Can you do that?

693
01:01:11,840 --> 01:01:14,195
- Do what?
- Keeping quiet.

694
01:01:14,280 --> 01:01:16,350
Say what you have to say!

695
01:01:18,480 --> 01:01:22,439
Last night, at around 4 in the morning,
I got up and left the apartment.

696
01:01:22,520 --> 01:01:23,839
- What?
- Dad!

697
01:01:25,240 --> 01:01:27,151
So I went out.

698
01:01:29,120 --> 01:01:30,997
I was wearing Jonathan's clothes.

699
01:01:31,080 --> 01:01:32,832
<i>And his shoes too.</i>

700
01:02:11,600 --> 01:02:13,716
PARIS STUDENT ID

701
01:03:26,800 --> 01:03:28,438
I don't know how I got back.

702
01:03:28,520 --> 01:03:29,873
Or how long it took.

703
01:03:30,560 --> 01:03:32,073
I suddenly saw the building,

704
01:03:32,840 --> 01:03:34,717
then the apartment door.

705
01:03:35,840 --> 01:03:40,436
I undressed in the bathroom.
Then I ran the hot water.

706
01:03:40,520 --> 01:03:41,999
Did you tell your brother?

707
01:03:47,640 --> 01:03:49,198
Did you tell your brother?

708
01:04:08,480 --> 01:04:10,550
Are you under the influence of alcohol?

709
01:04:14,160 --> 01:04:15,275
What?

710
01:04:16,040 --> 01:04:17,473
What is it, Paul?

711
01:04:18,680 --> 01:04:19,829
What is it?

712
01:04:22,920 --> 01:04:24,399
Paul, what's wrong?

713
01:04:24,600 --> 01:04:26,511
What are you looking at?
What is it?

714
01:04:28,080 --> 01:04:29,672
What is it? Look at me!

715
01:04:48,640 --> 01:04:50,358
But did you tell him?

716
01:04:50,440 --> 01:04:53,477
Yes, of course. He was there.
I couldn't not tell him.

717
01:04:53,560 --> 01:04:54,595
What did he say?

718
01:04:54,680 --> 01:04:57,240
He said if I do that again, he'll punch me out.

719
01:05:07,840 --> 01:05:09,717
For once, I agree with him.

720
01:05:12,160 --> 01:05:13,479
What is it?

721
01:05:13,560 --> 01:05:15,471
Remember me? I'm Alice.

722
01:05:15,560 --> 01:05:17,949
- Jonathan told me to drop by.
- He's not back yet.

723
01:05:18,040 --> 01:05:19,268
When will he be back?

724
01:05:19,360 --> 01:05:21,510
Lmpossible to know.

725
01:05:21,600 --> 01:05:22,749
He asked me to...

726
01:05:22,840 --> 01:05:24,910
Then come in!
Wait in here.

727
01:05:26,080 --> 01:05:27,229
This way.

728
01:05:29,960 --> 01:05:32,793
Have a seat on the couch. Watch TV.

729
01:05:34,200 --> 01:05:35,269
Excuse me.

730
01:05:37,320 --> 01:05:38,912
What the hell are you doing?

731
01:05:39,000 --> 01:05:40,592
Hungry? There's chicken soup.

732
01:05:43,480 --> 01:05:45,710
- Is this a joke?
- I'm going to bed.

733
01:05:51,080 --> 01:05:53,071
Sit on the couch!

734
01:05:57,920 --> 01:05:59,399
Wait, wait!

735
01:05:59,480 --> 01:06:01,596
Hitting me wasn't very nice.

736
01:06:01,680 --> 01:06:03,159
You're crazy!

737
01:06:04,520 --> 01:06:06,476
Don't leave me with her.
Who is she?

738
01:06:06,560 --> 01:06:08,039
Ask your brother.

739
01:06:19,040 --> 01:06:20,155
Good night.

740
01:06:29,160 --> 01:06:30,434
Good night!

741
01:06:50,720 --> 01:06:52,597
Is my brother an asshole?

742
01:06:58,840 --> 01:06:59,955
I see.

743
01:07:00,600 --> 01:07:03,034
We can talk bad about him,
so you'll feel better.

744
01:07:04,880 --> 01:07:06,279
Or talk nicely?

745
01:07:07,480 --> 01:07:08,469
No?

746
01:07:09,520 --> 01:07:11,112
Not talk about him at all?

747
01:07:12,720 --> 01:07:13,948
Keep quiet?

748
01:07:16,080 --> 01:07:17,354
Not that either?

749
01:07:20,640 --> 01:07:22,392
What should we talk about?

750
01:07:28,520 --> 01:07:32,433
I'm not the best conversationalist
these past few days.

751
01:07:41,560 --> 01:07:42,549
However...

752
01:07:44,040 --> 01:07:45,758
It's coming back some.

753
01:07:47,400 --> 01:07:49,550
But barely an hour ago.

754
01:07:50,640 --> 01:07:51,595
Above all...

755
01:07:52,840 --> 01:07:54,671
I won't hold out long alone.

756
01:08:00,440 --> 01:08:04,035
In this house, it's rare to not be interrupted.

757
01:08:04,120 --> 01:08:05,758
I lost the habit.

758
01:08:27,440 --> 01:08:31,115
Jon surely told you about our sister Claire.

759
01:08:31,200 --> 01:08:32,155
No?

760
01:08:35,600 --> 01:08:39,309
Don't be mad at him.
Certain silences can be wise.

761
01:08:42,560 --> 01:08:46,439
Anyway, we had a sister, Claire.

762
01:08:48,120 --> 01:08:52,033
I remember, once or twice a month

763
01:08:52,120 --> 01:08:57,069
she spent the whole day sobbing,
her nose in a tissue.

764
01:08:57,160 --> 01:08:59,754
Nothing could draw her away from heartache.

765
01:08:59,840 --> 01:09:03,674
Not the best jokes,
nor the biggest confessions.

766
01:09:03,760 --> 01:09:05,830
Attempts to distract her were in vain.

767
01:09:07,240 --> 01:09:09,879
That's because she cried
for absolutely no reason.

768
01:09:09,960 --> 01:09:11,757
She said it herself.

769
01:09:11,840 --> 01:09:13,717
A very old sorrow,

770
01:09:14,760 --> 01:09:17,911
so old she probably felt it the first time

771
01:09:18,000 --> 01:09:19,513
in a previous life...

772
01:09:20,640 --> 01:09:24,235
In the Middle Ages or in the times of idle kings.

773
01:09:35,320 --> 01:09:36,719
Ever since, you see

774
01:09:38,240 --> 01:09:41,550
this sadness kept coming back regularly.

775
01:09:42,080 --> 01:09:45,789
Impossible for Claire to escape it. Useless.

776
01:09:45,880 --> 01:09:47,757
She called them the blubbering days.

777
01:09:48,720 --> 01:09:51,359
She welcomed with laughter, like cousins.

778
01:09:52,040 --> 01:09:53,598
Her eyes stayed moist.

779
01:09:57,120 --> 01:10:01,159
I could have strangled her those days,
not being able to help her.

780
01:10:02,400 --> 01:10:04,197
I felt so humiliated.

781
01:10:07,680 --> 01:10:12,071
Like she was testing my helplessness
against others' suffering.

782
01:10:12,160 --> 01:10:14,276
So she cried to make you mad?

783
01:10:17,720 --> 01:10:19,631
It wasn't against me.

784
01:10:19,720 --> 01:10:21,312
She just cried.

785
01:10:21,400 --> 01:10:23,436
Like a Buddha or some divinity.

786
01:10:25,600 --> 01:10:29,798
It's impossible for others to admit
being able to cry that way.

787
01:10:30,240 --> 01:10:31,639
